      "text": "It was an honor to be a part of yesterday’s Mount Rushmore Naturalization Ceremony and welcome America's newest citizens in my home state of South Dakota. \n\nI’m so excited and proud of all these wonderful people who worked, read and studied for years to become citizens the RIGHT way. \n\nIt was so special for me to share the moment with them and congratulate them. We hugged, shed happy tears and shared the joy together.\n\nWelcome home, to the greatest country on earth!",
